		<b>Comment By Andy, 7-20-05</b>
		<p>I love the idea of citizen journalism, but YourHub isnâ€™t pulling it off. It doesnâ€™t help that the YourHub website is impossible to navigate. <br />
<br />
Perhaps Coloradoâ€™s flagship newspapers should shift the resources going into YourHub toward more community coverage within their existing papers and websites. <br />
<br />
Leaving it entirely up to citizens doesnâ€™t work. It would be interesting if each paper had a couple of full-time journalists who facilitate community stories by finding interesting people and helping them structure and write their own stories.</p>
		
		<b>Comment By John Temple, 7-31-05</b>
		<p>I appreciate Andy's suggestion. But perhaps he doesn't understand how YourHub.com works. We do have journalists assigned to each Web site and section, and they do contact people in the community and help them write or post stories, and they do write and post original stories themselves. In other words, we aren't leaving it entirely up to citizens. But we do believe that our YourHub.com journalists are facilitators in a way that writers for other sections of the Rocky aren't. Hope this helps.<br />
John Temple<br />
Editor, president and publisher<br />
Rocky Mountain News</p>
		
